<subSubSection id="B2B2652E1D2AFF9580B0FA8FFE42FD78" box="[151,392,1352,1378]" pageId="10" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="FA1736A51D2AFF9580B0FA8FFE42FD78" blockId="10.[151,392,1352,1378]" box="[151,392,1352,1378]" pageId="10">
<heading id="A15F81C91D2AFF9580B0FA8FFE42FD78" bold="true" box="[151,392,1352,1378]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="10" reason="1">
<emphasis id="C8DCEAB71D2AFF9580B0FA8FFE42FD78" bold="true" box="[151,392,1352,1378]" pageId="10">
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="3DA84D261D2AFF958139FA8FFE42FD78" box="[286,392,1352,1378]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Lotharia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C8DCEAB71D2AFF958139FA8FFE42FD78" bold="true" box="[286,392,1352,1378]" italics="true" pageId="10">Lotharia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B2B2652E1D2AFF9580B0FA49FD78FE65" pageId="10" type="description">
<paragraph id="FA1736A51D2AFF9580B0FA49FD78FE65" blockId="10.[151,1437,1422,1987]" pageId="10">
The species 
<taxonomicName id="3DA84D261D2AFF958100FA48FD7DFDBD" authority="Mandl, 1944" authorityName="Mandl" authorityYear="1944" box="[295,695,1422,1447]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Lotharia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angulicollis">
<emphasis id="C8DCEAB71D2AFF958100FA48FDD2FDBD" box="[295,536,1423,1447]" italics="true" pageId="10">Lotharia angulicollis</emphasis>
Mandl, 1944
</taxonomicName>
, the only representative of the genus, was described based on a single female. It is rather enigmatic because of its small size, external unique morphology and exceptional rarity. The description of the male led to the conclusion that this genus is phylogenetically close to 
<taxonomicName id="3DA84D261D2AFF95849BFA10FF11FE09" authority="Perreau 2003" authorityName="Perreau" authorityYear="2003" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Aphaobius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C8DCEAB71D2AFF95849BFA10FAFEFDF5" box="[1212,1332,1495,1519]" italics="true" pageId="10">Aphaobius</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="9E394B541D2AFF958563FA10FF1EFE09" author="Perreau" pageId="10" refString="Perreau, M. (2003) Contribution a la connaissance des Bathysciina de la &quot; serie d' Aphaobius &quot; (sensu Jeannel, 1924) (Coleoptera: Leiodidae, Cholevinae, Leptodirini). Annales de la Societe entomologique de France, (Nouvelle Serie), 39 (3), 211 - 224. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00379271.2003.10697377" type="journal article" year="2003">Perreau 2003</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The finding of another exemplar in the type locality allowed us to add this genus to the analyses, which confirmed its sister relationship with the genus 
<taxonomicName id="3DA84D261D2AFF958297F9D8FCE2FE2D" box="[688,808,1567,1591]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Aphaobius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C8DCEAB71D2AFF958297F9D8FCE2FE2D" box="[688,808,1567,1591]" italics="true" pageId="10">Aphaobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the inclusion of other species of 
<taxonomicName id="3DA84D261D2AFF95853AF9D8FA5FFE2D" box="[1309,1429,1567,1591]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Aphaobius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C8DCEAB71D2AFF95853AF9D8FA5FFE2D" box="[1309,1429,1567,1591]" italics="true" pageId="10">Aphaobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as well as 
<taxonomicName id="3DA84D261D2AFF95812BF984FDF9FE41" authority="Pretner, 1949" authorityName="Pretner" authorityYear="1949" box="[268,563,1603,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Aphaobiella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C8DCEAB71D2AFF95812BF984FE5FFE41" box="[268,405,1603,1627]" italics="true" pageId="10">Aphaobiella</emphasis>
Pretner, 1949
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="3DA84D261D2AFF95824CF984FCBAFE41" authority="Muller, 1931" authorityName="Muller" authorityYear="1931" box="[619,880,1602,1627]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Pretneria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C8DCEAB71D2AFF95824CF984FD1FFE40" box="[619,725,1603,1626]" italics="true" pageId="10">Pretneria</emphasis>
Müller, 1931
</taxonomicName>
, would be necessary to determine more precisely the phylogenetic position of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="3DA84D261D2AFF95826EF9A0FD61FE65" box="[585,683,1639,1663]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Lotharia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C8DCEAB71D2AFF95826EF9A0FD61FE65" box="[585,683,1639,1663]" italics="true" pageId="10">Lotharia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B2B2652E1D2AFF9580E0F94CFB8EFFD9" pageId="10" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="FA1736A51D2AFF9580E0F94CFA5AFF29" blockId="10.[151,1437,1422,1987]" pageId="10">
<taxonomicName id="3DA84D261D2AFF9580E0F94CFEF5FEB9" box="[199,319,1675,1699]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Aphaobius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C8DCEAB71D2AFF9580E0F94CFEF5FEB9" box="[199,319,1675,1699]" italics="true" pageId="10">Aphaobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
plus 
<taxonomicName id="3DA84D261D2AFF958159F94CFE2BFEB9" box="[382,481,1675,1699]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Lotharia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C8DCEAB71D2AFF958159F94CFE2BFEB9" box="[382,481,1675,1699]" italics="true" pageId="10">Lotharia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are part of a strongly supported clade including Leptodirini endemic to the Western Alps, from Brescia (
<collectingCountry id="82BF76351D2AFF9581A5F969FE72FEDD" box="[386,440,1710,1735]" name="Italy" pageId="10">Italy</collectingCountry>
) to 
<collectingCountry id="82BF76351D2AFF9581CFF969FD84FEDD" box="[488,590,1710,1735]" name="Slovenia" pageId="10">Slovenia</collectingCountry>
: 
<taxonomicName id="3DA84D261D2AFF95827BF968FC9AFEDD" authority="Miller, 1856" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1856" box="[604,848,1710,1735]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Oryotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C8DCEAB71D2AFF95827BF968FD7CFEDC" box="[604,694,1711,1734]" italics="true" pageId="10">Oryotus</emphasis>
Miller, 1856
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3DA84D261D2AFF95837AF968FBA6FEDD" authority="Muller, 1912" authorityName="Muller" authorityYear="1912" box="[861,1132,1710,1735]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Orostygia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C8DCEAB71D2AFF95837AF968FC06FEDC" box="[861,972,1711,1734]" italics="true" pageId="10">Orostygia</emphasis>
Müller, 1912
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3DA84D261D2AFF95845EF968FA56FEDD" authority="Paoletti, 1972" authorityName="Paoletti" authorityYear="1972" box="[1145,1436,1710,1735]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Cansiliella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C8DCEAB71D2AFF95845EF968FB3EFEDD" box="[1145,1268,1711,1735]" italics="true" pageId="10">Cansiliella</emphasis>
Paoletti, 1972
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="3DA84D261D2AFF9580EFF914FDC5FEF1" authority="Jeannel, 1911" authorityName="Jeannel" authorityYear="1911" box="[200,527,1746,1771]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Pholeuonidius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C8DCEAB71D2AFF9580EFF914FEA0FEF1" box="[200,362,1747,1771]" italics="true" pageId="10">Pholeuonidius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="9E394B541D2AFF958155F915FDC5FEF1" author="Jeannel" box="[370,527,1746,1771]" pageId="10" refString="Jeannel, R. (1911) Revision des Bathysciinae (Coleopteres Silphides). Morphologie, distribution geographique, systematique. Archives de Zoologie Experimentale et Generale, 47, 1 - 641. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 63151" type="journal article" year="1911">Jeannel, 1911</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, the last one sister to the rest. 
<bibRefCitation id="9E394B541D2AFF95834BF915FBC2FEF1" author="Vailati" box="[876,1032,1746,1771]" pageId="10" refString="Vailati, D. (1998) Ridescrizione di Orostygia tibialis Paoletti, 1979 (Coleoptera Cholevidae Leptodirinae) buona specie del massiccio Cansiglio-Monte Cavallo (Prealpi Venete). &quot; NATURA BRESCIANA &quot; Annali del Museo Civico di Scienze Naturali di Brescia, 31 [1995], 121 - 128." type="journal article" year="1998">Vailati (1998)</bibRefCitation>
identified as 
<taxonomicName id="3DA84D261D2AFF958483F914FF05FF15" authority="Muller, 1912" authorityName="Muller" authorityYear="1912" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Orostygia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="moczarskii">
<emphasis id="C8DCEAB71D2AFF958483F914FA8BFEF1" box="[1188,1345,1747,1771]" italics="true" pageId="10">O. moczarskii</emphasis>
Müller, 1912
</taxonomicName>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="3DA84D261D2AFF958153F930FE29FF14" box="[372,483,1783,1806]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Orostygia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C8DCEAB71D2AFF958153F930FE29FF14" box="[372,483,1783,1806]" italics="true" pageId="10">Orostygia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Grotta Vecchia Diga (
<collectingCountry id="82BF76351D2AFF958306F931FC9DFF15" box="[801,855,1782,1807]" name="Italy" pageId="10">Italy</collectingCountry>
, Pordenone, Valcellina). Subsequently, 
<bibRefCitation id="9E394B541D2AFF958530F931FA56FF15" author="Piva" box="[1303,1436,1782,1807]" pageId="10" refString="Piva, E. (2005) Nuove specie di Orostygia e Oryotus, con note sinonimiche (Coleoptera Cholevidae). Memorie della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 84, 3 - 44. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.4081 / memorieSEI. 2005.3" type="journal article" year="2005">Piva (2005)</bibRefCitation>
noted that these specimens should be ascribed to 
<taxonomicName id="3DA84D261D2AFF95829AF8DCFBDBFF29" authority="Porro &amp; Quaia, 1969" authorityName="Porro &amp; Quaia" authorityYear="1969" box="[701,1041,1818,1843]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Orostygia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rossii">
<emphasis id="C8DCEAB71D2AFF95829AF8DCFCD6FF28" box="[701,796,1819,1842]" italics="true" pageId="10">O. rossii</emphasis>
Porro &amp; Quaia, 1969
</taxonomicName>
, the name that we have used here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FA1736A51D2AFF9580E0F8F9FB8EFFD9" blockId="10.[151,1437,1422,1987]" pageId="10">
<materialsCitation id="4AC03CF81D2AFF9580E0F8F9FB8EFFD9" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1313779464" location="Kamnik" pageId="10" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Kamnik">
The discovery of a new species of 
<taxonomicName id="3DA84D261D2AFF958247F8F8FD12FF4D" box="[608,728,1855,1879]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Aphaobius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C8DCEAB71D2AFF958247F8F8FD12FF4D" box="[608,728,1855,1879]" italics="true" pageId="10">Aphaobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within the distribution area of 
<taxonomicName id="3DA84D261D2AFF958463F8F8FB72FF4D" box="[1092,1208,1855,1879]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Aphaobius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kraussi">
<emphasis id="C8DCEAB71D2AFF958463F8F8FB72FF4D" box="[1092,1208,1855,1879]" italics="true" pageId="10">A. kraussi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was unexpected. A careful examination of other specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="3DA84D261D2AFF9582A8F8A4FCCDFF61" box="[655,775,1891,1915]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Aphaobius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C8DCEAB71D2AFF9582A8F8A4FCCDFF61" box="[655,775,1891,1915]" italics="true" pageId="10">Aphaobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected in the area would be necessary, especially the populations of 
<taxonomicName id="3DA84D261D2AFF958166F840FE79FF85" box="[321,435,1927,1951]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Aphaobius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kraussi">
<emphasis id="C8DCEAB71D2AFF958166F840FE79FF85" box="[321,435,1927,1951]" italics="true" pageId="10">A. kraussi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingRegion id="386CF8471D2AFF958203F841FDB4FF85" box="[548,638,1926,1951]" country="Slovenia" name="Kamnik" pageId="10">Kamnik</collectingRegion>
–Savinja Alps (
<figureCitation id="62932A201D2AFF958309F841FCBEFF85" box="[814,884,1926,1951]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1503,1525]" captionTargetBox="[151,1429,700,1481]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[151,1436,700,1482]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 6. Distribution map of the genus Aphaobius in Austria and Slovenia. 1. A. kraussi; 2. A. brevicornis; 3. A. mixanigi; 4. A. haraldi sp. n." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258614/files/figure.png" pageId="10">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
), to determine more precisely if the new species has a wider distribution, and if it may be syntopic with 
<taxonomicName id="3DA84D261D2AFF958325F86CFCB8FFD9" box="[770,882,1963,1987]" class="Insecta" family="Leiodidae" genus="Aphaobius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kraussi">
<emphasis id="C8DCEAB71D2AFF958325F86CFCB8FFD9" box="[770,882,1963,1987]" italics="true" pageId="10">A. kraussi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in some localities.
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
